<h2>
	Focal Points
</h2>

<p>
	Each Image can be given a focal point, which means if the image is cropped to work with the design, you can choose the centre of the crop.
</p>

<p>
	To do this you need to click on the image once, and this will open a popup of the image with an <strong>Enable Focal Point</strong> button in the top right. Once clicked you will see a small circle appear on the image which you can drag to the main focal area. Once happy, you can click off from the image and save the entry to see your changes.
</p>

